         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ We, Friedrich Franz, by the Grace of God Grand Duke of Mecklenburg, Prince of Wenden, Schwerin and Ratzeburg, also Count of Schwerin, Sovereign of the Counties of Rostock and Stargard, etc., etc., ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">65.11.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Friedrich Franz II, Grand Duke of Mecklenburg</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M200a.35, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is a certificate with a seal blind-stamped in the lower left quarter.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">Friedrich Franz</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">von Gottes Gnaden Grossherzog von Mecklenburg, Fürst zu Wenden, Schwerin und Ratzeburg, auch Graf zu Schwerin, der Lande Rostock und Stargard Herr etc. etc.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wir bezeugen durch gegenwärtiges</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">Diplom</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">dass Wir den Dr Ferdinand Müller, Professor der Botanik an der Universität in Melbourne zum Ritter</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">des Hausordens der Wendischen Krone</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">in Grundlage des Statuts dieses Ordens ernannt haben.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">Schwerin den 9. November 1865.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="de">Friedrich Franz</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">J v Oertzen</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We, Friedrich Franz, by the Grace of God Grand Duke of Mecklenburg, Prince of Wenden, Schwerin and Ratzeburg, also Count of Schwerin, Sovereign of the Counties of Rostock and Stargard, etc., etc., testify by this Diploma, that we have created Dr Ferdinand Mueller, Professor of Botany at the University of Melbourne,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M was never a professor of the University of Melbourne.</p>
               </note> a Knight of the House-Order of the Wendish Crown in accordance with the statutes of this Order.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Schwerin, 9 November 1865.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Friedrich Franz.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">J v Oertzen<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Jasper von Oertzen. See also J. von Oertzen to M, 9 November 1865 (in this edition as 65-11-09a). An official announcement of M's appointment, dated Schwerin, 13 November 1865, was published in </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Regierungs-Blatt </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">für das Grossherzogthum Mecklenburg-Schwerin</seg>, No. 47, 1865, p. 293.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
